Other solutions:

  • The software used to create the model
  • Can do networked rendering
  • But only runs on Linux/Windows/OS X

  • Crowd-sourced Rendering
  • Powered by the BOINC Framework (SETI, Folding@Home)
  • Again, only runs on Linux/Windows/OS X

  • Cloud-based supercomputing
  • Interfaces with Blender
  • Scales-up to as many processing cores as required
  • At a cost... (US$0.30 per core hour)
